            "text_size": "40,15",
            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2>How to Tell If Your Saree’s the Real Deal</h2><h3></h3><h3><br/>The Zari Test</h3><p>Take a closer look at the zari threads. Real zari is usually silver dipped in gold, so when you scratch it lightly (just a gentle scratch!), you should see a hint of red or yellow underneath. If it looks white or plastic-y, that’s a red flag. Real zari keeps its shine without flaking off.</p><h3>Feel the Weave - Korvai Technique</h3><p>Run your fingers along the border where the saree’s body and pallu meet. In genuine Kanjeevarams, this joint is neat and strong, thanks to the Korvai technique. If you notice stitching or glue, that saree might not be authentic.</p>",
